alert.note: Alert for Dakota; Ramsey; Washington (Minnesota) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Warning issued April 20 at 9:22PM CDT until further notice by NWS Minneapolis
info.description: ...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Minnesota... Mississippi River at St. Paul affecting Ramsey, Washington and Dakota Counties. .Widespread flooding continues on area rivers. Additional rainfall from today and into Friday will keep river flows increased. ...FLOOD WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE... * WHAT...Moderate flooding is occurring and major flooding is forecast. * WHERE...Mississippi River at St. Paul. * WHEN...Until further notice. * IMPACTS...At 18.0 feet, Warner Road may become impassable due to high water. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 810 PM CDT Thursday, the stage was 16.3 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 810 PM CDT Thursday was 16.3 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to rise to 18.9 feet next Thursday evening. Additional rises are possible thereafter. - Flood stage is 14.0 feet. - Flood History...This crest compares to a previous crest of 18.8 feet on 04/16/1951. &&
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles.
